## 7.2.5 Definition of the Testing and Validation Samples

### Purpose
This subsection defines the out-of-sample evaluation protocol.

### Setup / formulation
Without regularization:

- train on one month and validate on the following non-overlapping month;
- or train on one thirty-minute interval and validate on the following non-overlapping interval.

With regularization:

- train on the initial sample;
- use the next sample as testing data to calibrate the regularization parameter;
- use the following sample as validation data for out-of-sample metrics.

### Main result
The chapter separates parameter fitting, regularization tuning, and out-of-sample validation.

### Interpretation
The validation sample must not be used for model selection. Otherwise, out-of-sample $R^2$ is contaminated by tuning bias.

