## 7.3.2 The Original OW Model

### Purpose
This subsection introduces the linear transient Obizhaeva-Wang impact model.

### Setup / formulation
The OW model is:

$$
I_{t+\delta t} - I_t
=
-\beta I_t \delta t
+
\lambda \sigma \frac{q_t}{ADV}.
$$

### Main result
OW is simple, tractable, and useful for analytical execution problems and equilibrium models.

### Interpretation
Trades move the impact state linearly, and impact decays exponentially over time. The model is not designed for highly variable liquidity or order-size concavity.

