## 7.3.3 The Locally Concave Bouchaud Model

### Purpose
This subsection introduces a locally concave propagator model.

### Setup / formulation
Bouchaud-style models use a concave local impact function. Empirical studies often find:

$$
g(x) \propto x^c,
\qquad
c \in [0.2,0.5].
$$

The square-root version is:

$$
I_{t+\delta t} - I_t
=
-\beta I_t \delta t
+
\lambda \sigma \operatorname{sign}(q_t)
\sqrt{\frac{|q_t|}{ADV}}.
$$

### Main result
The locally concave Bouchaud model performs well for fill-level simulation and short-horizon impact modeling.

### Interpretation
Concavity is applied to each local trade increment $q_t$. This is different from order-level concavity for a full metaorder or day order.

