## 7.3.4 The Reduced-Form Model

### Purpose
This subsection introduces a tractable model with dynamic liquidity or market activity.

### Setup / formulation
The reduced-form model is:

$$
I_{t+\delta t} - I_t
=
-\beta I_t \delta t
+
\frac{\lambda \sigma q_t}{\sqrt{ADV \cdot v_t}},
$$

where:

$$
v_{t+\delta t} - v_t
=
-\beta v_t \delta t
+
|q_t|.
$$

### Main result
The reduced-form model adjusts impact intensity according to market activity.

### Interpretation
When market activity is high, the same trade imbalance has less impact. This helps capture intraday liquidity variation and makes the model useful for stochastic control applications.

