## 7.3.5 The Globally Concave AFS Model

### Purpose
This subsection introduces the AFS model, which captures order-level concavity.

### Setup / formulation
The AFS model defines a latent state $J_t$:

$$
J_{t+\delta t} - J_t
=
-\beta J_t \delta t
+
\frac{q_t}{ADV}.
$$

Impact is then:

$$
I_t
=
\lambda \sigma \operatorname{sign}(J_t)
\sqrt{|J_t|}.
$$

### Main result
AFS applies concavity to accumulated resilient signed volume, not to each local fill.

### Interpretation
The model is better suited to sizable orders and risk-management applications than to fill-level impact simulation. It captures order-level concavity more directly than the locally concave Bouchaud model.

