### Main result
Price impact is strongest and model performance improves most near the start and end of the trading day. OFI benefits the most from non-parametric time-of-day fitting. The reduced-form model benefits the least because $v_t$ already captures some dynamic liquidity effects.

### Interpretation
Liquidity varies substantially intraday. A static model misses some of this variation, while a non-parametric intraday model captures it at the cost of lower stability.

