## 7.5.2.3 Counterfactuals Under $\mathcal{E}$

### Purpose
This subsection defines cross-impact counterfactuals under the factor-mediated causal graph.

### Setup / formulation
Stock-level cross-impact is:

$$
\mathbb{E}[\Delta P_j \mid do(\bar Q)].
$$

Factor-level cross-impact is:

$$
\mathbb{E}[\Delta \bar P \mid do(\bar Q)].
$$

Because $\bar Q$ has no parents in $\mathcal{E}$, the counterfactual is naively identifiable.

### Main result
Under $\mathcal{E}$, factor-level cross-impact can be identified without back-door adjustment.

### Interpretation
The factor flow is the action variable. Once the model is expressed at the factor level, the causal interpretation becomes cleaner than pairwise stock-to-stock estimation.

